Masashi...

5
00:00:31,440 --> 00:00:33,900
Masashi, are you okay?

6
00:00:36,520 --> 00:00:39,700
You don't have to be so formal to thank me.

7
00:00:39,700 --> 00:00:42,840
It was fun to drive for the first time in a while.

8
00:00:42,840 --> 00:00:46,520
I want my own car now.

9
00:00:47,660 --> 00:00:50,860
Well, I just said I wanted to go out with you.

10
00:00:50,860 --> 00:00:54,300
I would go with you to drink anytime.

11
00:00:54,300 --> 00:00:58,070
Did something happen at work? You don't seem to be yourself, being so timid and all.

12
00:00:58,070 --> 00:01:00,540
No, that's not what I meant, Junko.

13
00:01:00,540 --> 00:01:02,840
I don't want to hear...

14
00:01:04,420 --> 00:01:08,010
you say nothing great about graduating from the  University of Tokyo.

15
00:01:08,010 --> 00:01:12,840
<i>I went to the University of Tokyo, but it didn't make my life better.</i>

16
00:01:12,840 --> 00:01:16,570
I'm trying my heardest now to get him into the University of Tokyo

17
00:01:16,570 --> 00:01:19,950
so he can be happy.

18
00:01:20,800 --> 00:01:22,530
Jun...

19
00:01:26,680 --> 00:01:28,790
Yuri!

20
00:01:35,370 --> 00:01:38,550
What's wrong? What took you so long?

21
00:01:45,970 --> 00:01:48,130
Thanks.

22
00:01:48,130 --> 00:01:51,130
Well, a steamed meat bun, and...

23
00:01:51,130 --> 00:01:53,740
Where is the red bean paste one?

24
00:01:53,740 --> 00:01:56,920
Which one should I eat?

25
00:01:57,710 --> 00:02:01,950
I tried, right? I tried really hard, right?

26
00:02:01,950 --> 00:02:06,670
She should get it. 99.9 out of 100 people would notice it.

27
00:02:06,670 --> 00:02:09,900
She's clueless on another level.

28
00:02:09,900 --> 00:02:14,200
As clueless as Yoshimoto Imagawa who was ambushed by Nobunaga in Okehazama.

29
00:02:14,200 --> 00:02:17,990
I had no idea she has a severe case of obtuse.

30
00:02:17,990 --> 00:02:19,450
- Make him a drink.
- Sure.

31
00:02:19,450 --> 00:02:21,270
For me, too.

32
00:02:21,760 --> 00:02:27,330
Junko truly believes that nobody would ever like her.

33
00:02:27,330 --> 00:02:32,650
Ever since she failed the college exam, she's lost her confidence and closed the shutter unconsciously.

34
00:02:32,650 --> 00:02:36,200
It will be tough to pry it open.

35
00:02:36,200 --> 00:02:38,510
Man up!

36
00:02:38,510 --> 00:02:43,770
I will, but that pink boy...

37
00:02:43,770 --> 00:02:45,430
Yuri, right?

38
00:02:46,510 --> 00:02:50,800
I think he has feelings for Jun.

39
00:02:50,800 --> 00:02:52,140
- He does.
- What?

40
00:02:52,140 --> 00:02:54,640
A hot high school boy fell for her.

41
00:02:54,640 --> 00:02:56,810
Junko's life is changing for the better.

42
00:02:56,810 --> 00:02:59,580
It might be him who will open the shutter.

43
00:02:59,580 --> 00:03:02,070
- Cheers!
- That's possible.

44
00:03:02,070 --> 00:03:06,360
Just holding hands with a high school boy would induce estrogen.

45
00:03:06,360 --> 00:03:09,010
Right? It will.

46
00:03:09,010 --> 00:03:10,870
Estrogen...

47
00:03:11,730 --> 00:03:15,560
Wait, I thought you were rooting for me.

48
00:03:15,560 --> 00:03:20,210
I told you I'm on Junko's side.

49
00:03:20,210 --> 00:03:24,790
A hand of a high school boy is slender...

50
00:03:27,070 --> 00:03:29,340
"To" and "For"...

51
00:03:29,340 --> 00:03:32,120
<i>[The University of Tokyo, Science Majors Study Guide]</i>

52
00:03:42,980 --> 00:03:44,300
<i>[Sanno Seminar]</i>

53
00:03:44,300 --> 00:03:48,800
The name of the English utilitarian is...

54
00:03:48,800 --> 00:03:52,110
Bentham. He...

55
00:03:52,110 --> 00:03:56,340
theorized "the greatest happiness of the greatest number."

56
00:03:56,340 --> 00:03:59,570
Simply put,

57
00:03:59,570 --> 00:04:02,580
the happiness of each individual

58
00:04:02,580 --> 00:04:05,870
will increase the level of happiness in the nation.

59
00:04:05,870 --> 00:04:08,850
He said, not only the nobles and authorities, but

60
00:04:08,850 --> 00:04:12,790
an ordinary person like me should be happy, too.

61
00:04:12,790 --> 00:04:14,780
He was a merciful man.

62
00:04:14,780 --> 00:04:17,550
And Bentham said,

63
00:04:17,550 --> 00:04:18,920
<i>[Western Cultural History of the 19th Century]</i>

64
00:04:18,920 --> 00:04:21,310
By calculating pleasure and pain,

65
00:04:21,310 --> 00:04:23,650
you can measure happiness.

66
00:04:23,650 --> 00:04:25,620
How is Yakumo doing?

67
00:04:25,620 --> 00:04:28,780
Oh, he's back to work.

68
00:04:28,780 --> 00:04:32,910
He's thankful to you for helping him.

69
00:04:33,510 --> 00:04:35,620
Is he dating anyone?

70
00:04:35,620 --> 00:04:38,260
What? Masashi?

71
00:04:38,260 --> 00:04:43,690
He's always been popular. He's a trader who graduated from the University of Tokyo.

72
00:04:43,690 --> 00:04:48,460
His life has been easy. What a lucky guy.

73
00:04:48,460 --> 00:04:51,160
Next is...

74
00:04:51,160 --> 00:04:53,650
What is happiness?

75
00:04:54,580 --> 00:04:56,860
- What?
- Can you calculate it?

76
00:04:56,860 --> 00:04:59,670
Oh, are you talking about Bentham?

77
00:04:59,670 --> 00:05:02,450
It won't be in the exam,

78
00:05:02,450 --> 00:05:05,660
but if you are curious, I can bring you some materials next time.

79
00:05:08,190 --> 00:05:12,650
Listen, Yurian. Men can find a wife easily,

80
00:05:12,650 --> 00:05:16,920
after getting into the University of Tokyo. So hand in there.

81
00:05:16,920 --> 00:05:21,480
I will. I'm going to pass the exam and surpass Yakumo.

82
00:05:21,480 --> 00:05:22,690
Good.

83
00:05:22,690 --> 00:05:26,030
Hey, you two are too close.

84
00:05:26,030 --> 00:05:30,350
- Eto Mika.
- I've made up my mind.

85
00:05:30,350 --> 00:05:33,500
- I'm going to study literature at Kyoto University.
- What?

86
00:05:33,500 --> 00:05:37,090
If I pick up the elegant Kyoto dialect,

87
00:05:37,090 --> 00:05:40,210
that will make me the most popular girl.

88
00:05:40,210 --> 00:05:43,040
You will definitely fall for me, Kyo.

89
00:05:43,040 --> 00:05:46,320
A long-distance relationship turns me on.

90
00:05:46,320 --> 00:05:47,630
Let go of me.

91
00:05:47,630 --> 00:05:50,450
But, why all of a sudden?

92
00:05:52,190 --> 00:05:54,740
Kyo and I both have an impure motive,

93
00:05:54,740 --> 00:05:59,410
but we're more motivated than the kids around us. Right?

94
00:06:01,730 --> 00:06:05,990
Okay. In that case, master all the 11th grader's curriculums

95
00:06:05,990 --> 00:06:09,320
until the spring of your senior year and catch up to the rest.

96
00:06:09,320 --> 00:06:11,420
No break for you, even in Christmas and New Year's.

97
00:06:11,420 --> 00:06:14,420
- What?
- Will there be really enough time?

98
00:06:14,420 --> 00:06:18,960
It'll be fine. Normally, students in prestigious private schools

99
00:06:18,960 --> 00:06:22,450
who enroll in the University of Tokyo

100
00:06:22,450 --> 00:06:25,940
are already finished with the 12th grader's curriculums by now.

101
00:06:25,940 --> 00:06:29,940
<i>But students in public schools who pass the exam for the University of Tokyo</i>

102
00:06:29,940 --> 00:06:32,630
<i>study the 12th grader's curriculums</i>

103
00:06:32,630 --> 00:06:36,090
<i>in their senior year.</i>

104
00:06:36,090 --> 00:06:39,610
It's easier to solve it using linear programming.

105
00:06:39,610 --> 00:06:43,660
I haven't taught them Math-2 yet. So shut up and cook.

106
00:06:43,660 --> 00:06:45,560
Yes, Ma'am.

107
00:06:45,560 --> 00:06:49,120
<i>Unlike the prestigious private universities, the University of Tokyo and Kyoto University</i>

108
00:06:49,120 --> 00:06:54,340
<i>won't include extremely difficult questions that are not in the text books.</i>

109
00:06:54,340 --> 00:06:55,220
<i>[January 1th, 2018]</i>

110
00:06:55,220 --> 00:07:00,300
<i>They rather test the ability to think on their own.</i>

111
00:07:01,860 --> 00:07:04,400
<i>Therefore, for now...
[I wish Kyohei Yuri and Eto Mika will pass the exam]</i>

112
00:07:04,400 --> 00:07:06,730
<i>it's important to cover the basics.
[February, 2018]</i>

113
00:07:06,730 --> 00:07:10,180
Correct. This is linear programming.

114
00:07:10,180 --> 00:07:12,480
Here. It Kanetsugu Naoe chocolate.

115
00:07:12,480 --> 00:07:15,040
- Happy Valentine's Day!
- Thank you.
<i>[Feburary 14th, 2018]</i>

116
00:07:15,040 --> 00:07:18,010
You got a chocolate! Good for you!

117
00:07:18,010 --> 00:07:20,990
Now there appears Marie Antoinette.

118
00:07:20,990 --> 00:07:23,480
Do you know who is Marie Antoinette?

119
00:07:23,480 --> 00:07:27,720
She was the wife of Louis XVI. She was living a gorgeous life at the time.

120
00:07:27,720 --> 00:07:29,570
<i>Don't be flustered and hang in there!</i>

121
00:07:29,570 --> 00:07:32,720
<i>Congratulations on passing the exam for the University of Tokyo!</i>

122
00:07:32,720 --> 00:07:34,460
<i>[March, 2018]</i>

123
00:07:34,460 --> 00:07:38,980
Since I concentrate on studying math after the summer,

124
00:07:38,980 --> 00:07:41,550
- I was able to improve my score.
- As I thought, math is the key subject.

125
00:07:41,550 --> 00:07:44,360
And I got into the University of Tokyo.

126
00:07:44,360 --> 00:07:48,850
I'm really thankful to all the teachers at Sanno Seminar.
<i>[Can I see you tonight?]</i>

127
00:07:50,310 --> 00:07:53,900
<i>[I am]</i>

128
00:07:53,900 --> 00:07:56,000
<i>[I am now]</i>

129
00:07:56,000 --> 00:07:57,760
<i>[I am now in Russia]</i>

130
00:07:57,760 --> 00:07:59,950
<i>[I am now in Russia...]</i>

131
00:07:59,950 --> 00:08:02,100
Jun!

132
00:08:05,270 --> 00:08:08,170
<i>[April, 2018]</i>

133
00:08:08,170 --> 00:08:10,740
- Shall we get going now?
- Excuse us for leaving first.

134
00:08:10,740 --> 00:08:13,950
- Good work.
- I know a good restaurant.

135
00:08:13,950 --> 00:08:18,210
<i>- You know a lot of places.
- I do. Just leave it to me.</i>

136
00:08:18,210 --> 00:08:19,980
It was hard. Will you help me later?

137
00:08:19,980 --> 00:08:22,180
<i>Let's work on it together.</i>

138
00:08:22,180 --> 00:08:25,690
<i>Did you solve all the questions?</i>

139
00:08:27,560 --> 00:08:31,600
<i>[More than 90% pass their university entrance exam!]</i>

140
00:08:32,540 --> 00:08:37,250
You caught up! You've mastered the 11th grader's curriculums entirely.

141
00:08:38,230 --> 00:08:41,760
I'm proud to say that now you can move on to a 12th grader.

142
00:08:41,760 --> 00:08:43,890
Congratulations on passing the grade level.

143
00:08:43,890 --> 00:08:45,350
Thanks.

144
00:08:48,680 --> 00:08:51,190
Well done!

145
00:08:53,200 --> 00:08:56,920
How are things with your dad? Seeing you studying diligently-

146
00:08:56,920 --> 00:08:59,250
He doesn't care about me.

147
00:08:59,250 --> 00:09:03,890
At least... your mother must be delighted, isn't she?

148
00:09:12,430 --> 00:09:14,660
You pulled me out of the blue,

149
00:09:14,660 --> 00:09:18,900
I hurt my back. You startled me.

150
00:09:33,240 --> 00:09:37,030
<i>[A Story to Read When You First Fall in Love]</i>

151
00:09:37,030 --> 00:09:40,020
<i>[Minami High School]</i>

152
00:09:40,020 --> 00:09:41,940
<i>[Episode 4]</i>

153
00:09:50,050 --> 00:09:51,750
Hello?

154
00:10:02,400 --> 00:10:07,520
<i>[Nakagawa Chiropractic Clinic]</i>

155
00:10:08,860 --> 00:10:12,150
Hello? I'm cured, completely!

156
00:10:12,150 --> 00:10:15,770
The chiropractor you recommended has a divine touch.

157
00:10:15,770 --> 00:10:20,140
Glad to hear that. When you called me, I mistook you for a pervert.

158
00:10:20,140 --> 00:10:23,000
I feel great. It was amazing.

159
00:10:23,000 --> 00:10:26,930
<i>I heard you. You've been in a lot of pain.</i>

160
00:10:28,220 --> 00:10:33,100
Harumi, you're really capable, as I thought.

161
00:10:33,100 --> 00:10:37,700
Yuri's grades have improved a lot and he's the hot topic of our school.

162
00:10:37,700 --> 00:10:40,120
I'll do whatever I can to support him.

163
00:10:40,120 --> 00:10:42,720
Call me if you need anything.

164
00:10:44,110 --> 00:10:45,920
Thank you.

165
00:10:45,920 --> 00:10:48,930
His family situation is a bit complicated.

166
00:10:48,930 --> 00:10:53,000
Let's watch over him both at school and the cram school.

167
00:10:53,000 --> 00:10:55,620
Do you mean about his father?

168
00:10:55,620 --> 00:10:58,170
He's the part of the problems, but...

169
00:10:59,320 --> 00:11:01,170
His mom...

170
00:11:02,150 --> 00:11:04,900
passed away when he was in middle school.

171
00:11:04,900 --> 00:11:06,480
What?

172
00:11:07,210 --> 00:11:10,720
<i>He became a delinquent out of despair.</i>

173
00:11:12,820 --> 00:11:16,200
<i>His dad has been always busy so</i>

174
00:11:16,200 --> 00:11:20,140
<i>he's home alone most of the time.</i>

175
00:11:30,760 --> 00:11:32,260
I'm home.

176
00:11:32,260 --> 00:11:33,950
What was the sound?

177
00:11:33,950 --> 00:11:35,390
My walking stick.

178
00:11:35,390 --> 00:11:40,100
Back pain again? Go take a bath and keep yourself warm.

179
00:11:40,100 --> 00:11:42,180
Thank you.

180
00:11:47,410 --> 00:11:53,600
<i>How lonely he must've been in this world?</i>

181
00:11:55,660 --> 00:11:58,470
- Wow, that's nice.
- I'm No. 8.

182
00:11:58,470 --> 00:12:00,220
Really?

183
00:12:11,970 --> 00:12:16,540
Yuri-yuri, here is an application form for the training camp.
<i>[Study Camp to Overcome Your Weakness]</i>

184
00:12:16,540 --> 00:12:19,310
With your parents' consent...

185
00:12:20,650 --> 00:12:26,460
With your parent's consent, can you have him stamp his seal here?

186
00:12:26,460 --> 00:12:31,550
Got it. He wouldn't oppose it.

187
00:12:31,550 --> 00:12:36,610
I'm so happy that I'll be able to teach you the entire time.

188
00:12:36,610 --> 00:12:40,780
If possible, I wish to go alone with you.

189
00:12:40,780 --> 00:12:43,890
That statement was inappropriate!

190
00:12:43,890 --> 00:12:49,060
He'll definitely improve if he gets a private lesson for four days straight.

191
00:12:49,060 --> 00:12:51,580
This will be the fastest way.

192
00:12:51,580 --> 00:12:53,920
Does that mean you two will sleep in the same room?

193
00:12:53,920 --> 00:12:56,670
I'm just kidding. He's only seventeen.

194
00:12:56,670 --> 00:13:00,130
I would be arrested!

195
00:13:00,770 --> 00:13:05,900
Oh, right! I made this for you, Yuri-yuri.

196
00:13:05,900 --> 00:13:07,890
A booklet for the study camp?
<i>[A booklet for the study camp during the Golden Week]</i>

197
00:13:07,890 --> 00:13:09,260
Where is mine?

198
00:13:09,260 --> 00:13:12,510
You'll be fine without it, won't you, Eto Mika?

199
00:13:12,510 --> 00:13:16,390
I even made a checklist so that you won't forget anything.

200
00:13:16,390 --> 00:13:20,640
- Don't forget to bring your dictionary. Here.
- Somehow...

201
00:13:20,640 --> 00:13:22,770
you sound like a mom.

202
00:13:22,770 --> 00:13:25,600
Not a mom. I'm more like a dad.

203
00:13:25,600 --> 00:13:29,880
There are a lot of non-traditional families nowadays.

204
00:13:29,880 --> 00:13:31,880
And everyone has maternal instinct.

205
00:13:31,880 --> 00:13:34,280
Maternal instinct?

206
00:13:34,280 --> 00:13:35,860
Did something happen with your mom?

207
00:13:35,860 --> 00:13:39,580
Hey now. Oh, right! A pillow!

208
00:13:39,580 --> 00:13:42,030
Do you need your own pillow for a good night's sleep?

209
00:13:42,030 --> 00:13:45,330
Sleep deprivation is not good, Yuri-chan.

210
00:13:47,220 --> 00:13:48,810
You can have it.

211
00:13:51,310 --> 00:13:54,330
- What's wrong, Yuri-chan? Wait.
- I'm leaving.

212
00:13:54,330 --> 00:13:57,790
Yuri-chan, what's wrong?

213
00:13:57,790 --> 00:14:01,460
You're really insensitive to people's feelings.

214
00:14:01,460 --> 00:14:05,880
Really? I'm trying my best, though.

215
00:14:10,120 --> 00:14:11,960
On top of his studies,

216
00:14:11,960 --> 00:14:16,850
I'm worried about him if he's eating or sleeping well.

217
00:14:16,850 --> 00:14:19,060
What are you, his mom?

218
00:14:19,060 --> 00:14:21,540
After missing the chance to marry,

219
00:14:21,540 --> 00:14:25,380
my maternal instinct of a thirty-something-year-old woman is overflowing.

220
00:14:26,160 --> 00:14:30,770
I'm really hopeless. I should go home and pet my dog.

221
00:14:30,770 --> 00:14:32,620
Is it really maternal instinct?

222
00:14:32,620 --> 00:14:35,180
It's not? Is it some kind of disease?

223
00:14:35,180 --> 00:14:38,510
No. Well I don't know.

224
00:14:38,510 --> 00:14:43,870
In any case, you're my first love, Harumi.

225
00:14:45,070 --> 00:14:48,770
So I'd like to see you live a happy life.

226
00:14:49,400 --> 00:14:53,370
By the way, since when did you become such a nice person?

227
00:14:53,370 --> 00:14:58,080
Well... I just thought this world would be a better place,

228
00:14:58,080 --> 00:15:00,780
if people like you are happy.

229
00:15:00,780 --> 00:15:03,730
"The greatest happiness of the greatest number."

230
00:15:03,730 --> 00:15:04,770
Bentham?

231
00:15:04,770 --> 00:15:08,170
- Do you remember that?
- For your information, I'm a sociology teacher.

232
00:15:08,170 --> 00:15:10,460
- Are you now?
- Geez.

233
00:15:10,460 --> 00:15:14,250
You're really dense, Junko.

234
00:15:14,250 --> 00:15:19,210
I asked you out many times before confessing to you. But you never noticed my feelings.

235
00:15:19,210 --> 00:15:21,300
I didn't?

236
00:15:21,300 --> 00:15:24,620
I feel sorry for guys who fall for you.

237
00:15:26,960 --> 00:15:31,040
I envy those who happily married in young age.

238
00:15:31,040 --> 00:15:34,060
What's happiness, anyway?

239
00:15:34,060 --> 00:15:36,580
You don't think about what happiness is

240
00:15:36,580 --> 00:15:39,980
when you're living a happy life.

241
00:15:39,980 --> 00:15:42,170
Indeed.

242
00:15:46,860 --> 00:15:52,520
<i>Even after knowing Yamashita is married, it's nice and comfortable</i>

243
00:15:52,520 --> 00:15:55,210
<i>to hang out with him as a friend.</i>

244
00:15:58,730 --> 00:16:00,590
<i>[Income Call: Masashi]</i>

245
00:16:03,760 --> 00:16:06,830
I'm out drinking now.

246
00:16:10,710 --> 00:16:12,920
Sorry.

247
00:16:12,920 --> 00:16:15,130
I'll be home soon.

248
00:16:18,920 --> 00:16:22,360
Plans for the Golden Week?
<i>(T/N: Holidays from April 29 to May 5th)</i>

249
00:16:22,360 --> 00:16:24,380
I'm attending the study camp for my school.

250
00:16:24,380 --> 00:16:28,460
It's a good opportunity to tutor Yuri-yuri all day long.

251
00:16:29,360 --> 00:16:32,370
Of course, I'll be staying in a hotel for three nights.

252
00:16:32,370 --> 00:16:35,460
What? Hello, Masashi?

253
00:16:35,460 --> 00:16:37,690
Hello?

254
00:16:37,690 --> 00:16:41,110
- Kato, you're here. Good morning.
- Good morning.

255
00:16:41,110 --> 00:16:45,720
<i>When we arrive at the camp site, we will have a placement test first.</i>

256
00:16:45,720 --> 00:16:49,300
<i>Your seat will be assigned according to your score.</i>

257
00:16:49,300 --> 00:16:50,590
<i>Okay.</i>

258
00:16:50,590 --> 00:16:54,000
We will have another test on the third day.

259
00:16:54,000 --> 00:16:58,620
Top students will be rewarded, so please work hard.

260
00:16:58,620 --> 00:17:01,510
- Seriously?
- Hey.

261
00:17:01,510 --> 00:17:03,090
Good morning.

262
00:17:03,090 --> 00:17:06,210
- Good morning!
- Good morning to you!

263
00:17:06,210 --> 00:17:08,080
What's the reward?

264
00:17:08,080 --> 00:17:11,120
You will find that out later.

265
00:17:14,460 --> 00:17:16,970
Here is the schedule for the camp.

266
00:17:24,250 --> 00:17:28,200
The first place's reward is a tablet for your studies!

267
00:17:28,200 --> 00:17:29,890
<i>Wow!</i>

268
00:17:29,890 --> 00:17:33,210
An electric dictionary for the second place.

269
00:17:33,210 --> 00:17:37,200
Â¥10,000 book gift card for the third place.

270
00:17:37,200 --> 00:17:42,030
To top it off, there are lucky items for passing exams.

271
00:17:42,030 --> 00:17:44,780
Slip-resistant socks!

272
00:17:44,780 --> 00:17:48,510
I also have here, good-luck candies.

273
00:17:48,510 --> 00:17:51,690
- Strawberry, melon, grape, orange flavors.
- Who would want that?

274
00:17:51,690 --> 00:17:56,540
You may gain the ability to memorize after eating it.

275
00:17:58,140 --> 00:18:00,320
Kyo. Kyo.

276
00:18:04,430 --> 00:18:07,180
Wait. There's no sound.

277
00:18:09,380 --> 00:18:12,760
No replies? Were you rejected?

278
00:18:12,760 --> 00:18:15,510
- What did you say?
- What?

279
00:18:17,540 --> 00:18:20,030
- Oh,  I got a reply!
- Oh, good.

280
00:18:20,030 --> 00:18:22,510
You should share it in the Timeline on LINE.

281
00:18:22,510 --> 00:18:26,000
Hey, what are you doing?

282
00:18:26,000 --> 00:18:29,110
- Oh, geez.
- That's crazy.

283
00:18:30,100 --> 00:18:31,780
I know, right?

284
00:18:44,400 --> 00:18:47,730
Come on, guys. Get off the bus.

285
00:18:47,730 --> 00:18:52,190
We'll have the test to overcome your weakness.

286
00:18:52,190 --> 00:18:54,820
Idiots are too easy to deceive.

287
00:18:54,820 --> 00:18:57,120
I see she likes you. Why don't you date her?

288
00:18:57,120 --> 00:18:58,910
Don't be ridiculous.

289
00:18:58,910 --> 00:19:00,730
<i>If you're ready...</i>

290
00:19:00,730 --> 00:19:03,000
- Hey!
- Hey!

291
00:19:03,000 --> 00:19:06,470
"Actually I've liked you for a long time, Ohtsuka. I mean it."

292
00:19:06,470 --> 00:19:08,730
- "For real?"
- "Yes."

293
00:19:08,730 --> 00:19:11,080
"I like you. Go out with me."

294
00:19:11,080 --> 00:19:13,610
"Sure, I would love to."

295
00:19:13,610 --> 00:19:18,000
"Of course I'm lying. It's hilarious. Can I share this in the Timeline?"

296
00:19:18,660 --> 00:19:21,140
What a jerk. A prank love confession?

297
00:19:21,140 --> 00:19:24,620
We were teasing her. It was just a game.

298
00:19:24,620 --> 00:19:26,430
She's crying, though.

299
00:19:26,430 --> 00:19:28,760
Please delete them.

300
00:19:28,760 --> 00:19:30,910
Give it back!

301
00:19:30,910 --> 00:19:33,070
What are you, middle schoolers?

302
00:19:33,690 --> 00:19:37,190
I bet you are not popular among girls.

303
00:19:37,190 --> 00:19:40,770
I bet you have never confessed or been confessed to in your life.

304
00:19:40,770 --> 00:19:42,920
That's why you treat others like trash.

305
00:19:42,920 --> 00:19:45,350
What did you say? Give it back.

306
00:19:45,350 --> 00:19:47,550
Let go.

307
00:19:47,550 --> 00:19:48,900
Ouch!

308
00:19:48,900 --> 00:19:50,930
I can't study with an annoying guy like you around.

309
00:19:50,930 --> 00:19:52,280
What did you say, you idiot?

310
00:19:52,280 --> 00:19:55,360
Guys, what's going on there?

311
00:19:55,360 --> 00:19:57,420
What's with the commotion?

312
00:19:57,420 --> 00:19:59,980
Stay calm. Enjoy your seminar life without a fuss, okay?

313
00:19:59,980 --> 00:20:03,390
The test starts in ten minutes.

314
00:20:03,390 --> 00:20:06,940
Get your belongings. The test will begin.

315
00:20:06,940 --> 00:20:08,620
Kyo, you're so cool.

316
00:20:08,620 --> 00:20:09,960
<i>Hurry up.</i>

317
00:20:09,960 --> 00:20:12,650
- Come on, guys. Let's get moving.
- Okay.

318
00:20:15,270 --> 00:20:17,940
<i>[Study Camp to Overcome Your Weakness]</i>

319
00:20:21,920 --> 00:20:26,990
Alright. We'll begin the first test to overcome your weakness.

320
00:20:26,990 --> 00:20:28,610
Start!

321
00:20:44,090 --> 00:20:47,480
Okay? The result here

322
00:20:47,480 --> 00:20:49,750
is your current academic ability.

323
00:20:49,750 --> 00:20:51,730
Okay? Take a look.

324
00:20:51,730 --> 00:20:55,070
- There I am!
- 38th place. That's impressive.

325
00:20:55,070 --> 00:20:56,750
<i>[1st: Naoto Ito. 2nd: Ryosuke Aikawa.]</i>

326
00:20:56,750 --> 00:21:01,390
I'm third. I beat Chosokabe, at least.
<i>[3rd: Hikaru Washitsu. 4th: Kei Chosokabe.]</i>

327
00:21:03,240 --> 00:21:05,530
Washizu, look at him.

328
00:21:05,530 --> 00:21:06,650
<i>[47th: Kyohei Yuri. 48th: Mai Sugiyama.]</i>

329
00:21:06,650 --> 00:21:08,520
He's 47th, the pink guy.

330
00:21:08,520 --> 00:21:12,640
What an idiot. He should give up already.

331
00:21:12,640 --> 00:21:13,690
There's no way he can get into the University of Tokyo.

332
00:21:13,690 --> 00:21:15,770
<i>When you study for the college exam,</i>

333
00:21:15,770 --> 00:21:19,880
<i>you should never be satisfied with your current level.</i>

334
00:21:28,360 --> 00:21:30,970
<i>[Incoming Video Call]</i>

335
00:21:30,970 --> 00:21:35,630
<i>How are you doing? This is fabulous Miwa.</i>

336
00:21:35,630 --> 00:21:38,460
<i>Wait, don't hang up.</i>

337
00:21:38,460 --> 00:21:43,310
<i>I wanted to tell you something important, so I got your number from Kabu.</i>

338
00:21:43,310 --> 00:21:45,540
Hamburg steak again?

339
00:21:45,540 --> 00:21:48,670
<i>Can you go somewhere quiet?</i>

340
00:21:48,670 --> 00:21:51,020
Hold on.

341
00:21:53,600 --> 00:21:57,470
<i>Alright. Now, let me get straight to the point.</i>

342
00:21:58,180 --> 00:22:01,760
<i>It's not annoying.</i>

343
00:22:01,760 --> 00:22:04,900
<i>Would it be annoying? If a high schooler </i>

344
00:22:04,900 --> 00:22:07,310
<i>confesses his love to a 32-year-old woman,</i>

345
00:22:07,310 --> 00:22:09,390
<i>would it be annoying?</i>

346
00:22:09,390 --> 00:22:14,830
<i>It's not annoying and I find it very entertaining. However</i>

347
00:22:14,830 --> 00:22:17,690
<i>you can't do anything until your 18th birthday!</i>

348
00:22:17,690 --> 00:22:22,330
<i>If she violates the law, she will die of shock. So resist it no matter what.</i>

349
00:22:23,570 --> 00:22:26,920
- Kyo, there you are.
<i>- Good luck to you!</i>

350
00:22:26,920 --> 00:22:29,240
What are you doing out here?

351
00:22:29,240 --> 00:22:30,570
Nothing really.

352
00:22:30,570 --> 00:22:32,950
There aren't any people around. I love this place.

353
00:22:32,950 --> 00:22:34,550
What are you doing?

354
00:22:34,550 --> 00:22:35,770
I have something to tell you.

355
00:22:35,770 --> 00:22:37,960
The two idiots are flirting.

356
00:22:37,960 --> 00:22:41,350
We came to the camp to improve our scores.

357
00:22:41,350 --> 00:22:43,460
We can't focus on our study with those guys around.

358
00:22:43,460 --> 00:22:46,090
It's better to study at the cram school.

359
00:22:47,200 --> 00:22:49,530
What's with his hair?

360
00:22:49,530 --> 00:22:53,120
Oh yeah. I should call my father and have him complain to the school.

361
00:22:53,120 --> 00:22:55,670
Good idea. Let's make a complaint.

362
00:22:55,670 --> 00:22:57,690
You guys,

363
00:22:58,370 --> 00:23:03,590
there may be people with blond hair or blue hair at the examination venue.

364
00:23:05,570 --> 00:23:11,090
If you can only concentrate in the most comfortable environment, you'll be in trouble.

365
00:23:11,090 --> 00:23:13,080
That's one of the reasons for holding this camp.

366
00:23:13,080 --> 00:23:17,770
Our intellect is totally different from that idiot.

367
00:23:17,770 --> 00:23:22,230
I'm sorry to inform you, but the test result shows it all.

368
00:23:22,230 --> 00:23:27,360
That's the most unfortunate things to hear from our students.

369
00:23:29,300 --> 00:23:35,660
Because I know you are sacrificing your free time for your study.

370
00:23:37,090 --> 00:23:41,100
You try so hard, and the result of your hard work

371
00:23:41,100 --> 00:23:45,780
is to look down on others? That's pathetic.

372
00:23:46,570 --> 00:23:51,110
We are teaching you so you can have a bright future.

373
00:23:51,940 --> 00:23:54,200
Excuse us.

374
00:23:58,020 --> 00:24:00,380
You're as cool as ever.

375
00:24:01,350 --> 00:24:04,160
Who... Masashi?

376
00:24:04,160 --> 00:24:06,000
Why are you here?

377
00:24:06,000 --> 00:24:09,460
Our company's resort is nearby,

378
00:24:09,460 --> 00:24:14,130
so I rode a bus to get here. Then... what a coincidence!

379
00:24:14,880 --> 00:24:16,220
I'm all alone.

380
00:24:16,220 --> 00:24:19,900
Why don't you come over for a drink after work? There is an open air bath with a great view.

381
00:24:19,900 --> 00:24:21,190
You were relegated?

382
00:24:21,190 --> 00:24:24,690
Relegated? I'm not.

383
00:24:24,690 --> 00:24:27,490
Training... Yeah, training.

384
00:24:27,490 --> 00:24:30,250
I came to the leadership training held by our company.

385
00:24:30,250 --> 00:24:32,500
It was decided at the last minute.

386
00:24:32,500 --> 00:24:35,740
I see.

387
00:24:35,740 --> 00:24:37,170
Right.

388
00:24:37,170 --> 00:24:40,950
I brought souvenirs for everyone.

389
00:24:40,950 --> 00:24:43,290
Oh, thank you.

390
00:24:43,290 --> 00:24:46,220
It's important to show courtesy at a workplace in Japan.

391
00:24:46,220 --> 00:24:47,760
If you look at the world...

392
00:24:47,760 --> 00:24:49,340
- Harumi-sensei!
- A souvenir...

393
00:24:49,340 --> 00:24:51,750
We have to practice!

394
00:24:51,750 --> 00:24:54,510
Sorry, I'll be right there!

395
00:24:54,510 --> 00:24:57,270
Thanks. See you!

396
00:25:03,780 --> 00:25:06,130
Three days left.

397
00:25:16,080 --> 00:25:17,520
Hi, there.

398
00:25:21,450 --> 00:25:23,560
Thanks for your help the other day.

399
00:25:24,720 --> 00:25:27,840
I just found out that my company's resort is nearby

400
00:25:27,840 --> 00:25:30,710
and I have a training there.

401
00:25:31,900 --> 00:25:34,560
If you would like, come hang out with us.

402
00:25:35,650 --> 00:25:37,040
See you.

403
00:25:41,270 --> 00:25:42,820
Wait.

404
00:25:48,960 --> 00:25:50,800
Masashi!

405
00:25:50,800 --> 00:25:52,170
Yes?

406
00:25:52,170 --> 00:25:55,320
- You forgot this.
- Thanks.

407
00:25:55,320 --> 00:25:57,150
It's quite cold outside.

408
00:25:57,150 --> 00:25:59,770
It is. You must be cold.

409
00:25:59,770 --> 00:26:02,950
I forgot to bring a jacket because I left in a hurry this morning.

410
00:26:02,950 --> 00:26:04,350
What?

411
00:26:04,880 --> 00:26:06,520
Then...

412
00:26:06,520 --> 00:26:10,570
I'll lend you this. I have another one back at the hotel.

413
00:26:11,180 --> 00:26:12,930
Thanks.

414
00:26:12,930 --> 00:26:17,450
Then I'll give you this in return.

415
00:26:17,450 --> 00:26:18,750
What's this?

416
00:26:18,750 --> 00:26:21,950
It's a reward for the students. Good-luck candy.

417
00:26:21,950 --> 00:26:23,670
Thanks.

418
00:26:23,670 --> 00:26:28,180
Is the open-air bath open till late hour?

419
00:26:28,180 --> 00:26:32,670
Yeah. It's open 24 hours. Come anytime.

420
00:26:32,670 --> 00:26:34,240
Great!

421
00:26:35,040 --> 00:26:37,600
Yuri-yuri, where are you going?

422
00:26:37,600 --> 00:26:38,680
For a walk.

423
00:26:38,680 --> 00:26:43,740
You can't! Your lesson will start soon! You can't be late.

424
00:26:43,740 --> 00:26:45,550
I know.

425
00:26:45,550 --> 00:26:48,780
If you know, don't go. We're at a study camp.

426
00:26:48,780 --> 00:26:51,510
Don't tell me what to do. You're annoying.

427
00:27:02,290 --> 00:27:05,550
What's wrong with him? I wonder if something happened.

428
00:27:06,590 --> 00:27:11,780
Human brains can't process negative statements.

429
00:27:14,920 --> 00:27:16,690
<i>[Test Rank: First Place]</i>

430
00:27:16,690 --> 00:27:18,750
<i>[Test Rank: Second Place]</i>

431
00:27:18,750 --> 00:27:21,590
That's the right answer. Excellent.

432
00:27:22,700 --> 00:27:28,190
The theorem is the basic of the trigonometric function. You have to memorize it.

433
00:27:28,190 --> 00:27:31,880
Harumi, can you help me for a second?

434
00:27:33,970 --> 00:27:36,270
What does this emphasis mean?

435
00:27:36,270 --> 00:27:39,480
Let's see. Oh, here?

436
00:27:39,480 --> 00:27:42,860
The word "the picture" is not a verb, so when you...

437
00:27:42,860 --> 00:27:48,380
That woman wants to send the pink hair to the University of Tokyo.

438
00:27:48,380 --> 00:27:50,030
And that girl

439
00:27:50,030 --> 00:27:53,260
joined the school to pursue the pink hair.

440
00:27:53,260 --> 00:27:55,850
He's getting on my nerve. He's just a delinquent.

441
00:27:55,850 --> 00:27:57,480
Right?

442
00:27:57,480 --> 00:27:59,720
I think he's cool.

443
00:28:01,650 --> 00:28:04,110
Unlike you guys.

444
00:28:07,520 --> 00:28:11,210
We'll prepare some towels. Please bring towels.

445
00:28:12,640 --> 00:28:16,620
We can go into the open-air bath...

446
00:28:17,500 --> 00:28:19,850
We can't go in.

447
00:28:20,750 --> 00:28:23,370
We can't!

448
00:28:31,990 --> 00:28:34,450
Hello?

449
00:28:40,970 --> 00:28:44,680
- Teacher, do you know where Kyo is?
- What?

450
00:28:44,680 --> 00:28:49,320
I can't find him anywhere. He's not in the boys' room either.

451
00:28:49,320 --> 00:28:51,990
No, I haven't seen him.

452
00:28:51,990 --> 00:28:54,960
A boy with pink hair would stand out, so...

453
00:28:54,960 --> 00:28:56,360
If you're looking for Yuri,

454
00:28:56,360 --> 00:28:59,750
he was smoking in the lodge on the hill behind.

455
00:28:59,750 --> 00:29:01,570
Is that true?

456
00:29:01,570 --> 00:29:03,610
We saw him while we were taking a walk.

457
00:29:03,610 --> 00:29:05,750
Having a hair like that,

458
00:29:05,750 --> 00:29:07,960
we were afraid that he would punch us if we say something to him.

459
00:29:07,960 --> 00:29:11,530
I bet you don't have that kind of friend around you.

460
00:29:11,530 --> 00:29:13,380
I'll go check on him.

461
00:29:13,380 --> 00:29:16,780
What, wait. Harumi-sensei!

462
00:29:19,610 --> 00:29:23,510
<i>I don't believe he would do such a thing.</i>

463
00:29:23,510 --> 00:29:25,770
<i>But today</i>

464
00:29:25,770 --> 00:29:28,040
<i>I couldn't stop him</i>

465
00:29:28,040 --> 00:29:30,480
<i>when he was shutting me out.</i>

466
00:29:31,980 --> 00:29:34,150
<i>I didn't know.</i>

467
00:29:42,790 --> 00:29:46,350
I'm sorry, Masashi.

468
00:29:46,350 --> 00:29:49,750
<i>Actually, I don't really care if he smoked or not.</i>

469
00:29:50,930 --> 00:29:53,860
<i>If he is suffering now,</i>

470
00:29:53,860 --> 00:29:56,430
<i>I'm more worried about that.</i>

471
00:29:59,740 --> 00:30:02,880
<i>What's that? A monkey? A wild boar?</i>

472
00:30:02,880 --> 00:30:05,860
<i>No, it's something bigger.</i>

473
00:30:05,860 --> 00:30:08,210
<i>Don't tell me...</i>

474
00:30:08,210 --> 00:30:10,310
Is it a bear?

475
00:30:20,820 --> 00:30:24,180
Yuri-yuri?

476
00:30:24,180 --> 00:30:26,550
They said you headed to the lodge and never came back.

477
00:30:26,550 --> 00:30:30,320
Is your back hurt? Should I carry you on my back?

478
00:30:32,830 --> 00:30:35,630
- Ouch! It hurts.
- Are you all right?

479
00:30:38,730 --> 00:30:40,590
Where were you headed to?

480
00:30:40,590 --> 00:30:42,600
Take me to the lodge.

481
00:30:42,600 --> 00:30:44,780
There's something I want to confirm.

482
00:30:44,780 --> 00:30:45,920
Is your back okay?

483
00:30:45,920 --> 00:30:47,790
I was a little tired from practice.

484
00:30:47,790 --> 00:30:49,080
Practice?

485
00:30:49,080 --> 00:30:50,650
- Let's go.
- Okay.

486
00:30:53,320 --> 00:30:57,070
<i>[Minami-Boso Community Lodge]</i>

487
00:31:00,960 --> 00:31:02,550
Is that it?

488
00:31:02,550 --> 00:31:04,340
I think so.

489
00:31:16,080 --> 00:31:18,840
How meticulous of them.

490
00:31:18,840 --> 00:31:21,460
The boys bought it.

491
00:31:24,840 --> 00:31:27,570
I'm sorry for leaving without a word.

492
00:31:28,710 --> 00:31:31,720
I went over to Yakumo's room.

493
00:31:31,720 --> 00:31:36,050
After he brought me back, I had a talk with the manager.

494
00:31:36,770 --> 00:31:39,250
So I think they know I was falsely accused.

495
00:31:41,100 --> 00:31:42,920
I had something I wanted to ask him.

496
00:31:42,920 --> 00:31:45,410
Like what?

497
00:31:48,120 --> 00:31:50,870
If you want Masashi to help with your studies,

498
00:31:50,870 --> 00:31:54,220
you should have said that in the first place.

499
00:31:56,250 --> 00:32:01,070
Well, Masashi is much more knowledgeable about science than I am,

500
00:32:01,070 --> 00:32:04,000
so let's ask him to help from now on.

501
00:32:06,080 --> 00:32:09,760
<i>- You like her, don't you?
- What?</i>

502
00:32:14,150 --> 00:32:16,130
<i>About Harumi.</i>

503
